  "title": "Meta Q3 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-10-29T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q3",
  "location": "Menlo Park, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.fb.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "mark-zuckerberg",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Zuckerberg",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q3 2025 revenue was $51.8 billion, up 19%. Meta AI now has 1.75 billion monthly active users — on track for 2 billion by year-end. AI-driven ad targeting improved our revenue per user by approximately 22% year-over-year in the US. WhatsApp Business is now generating over $1 billion in quarterly revenue. We are on track to ship Llama 5 before the end of Q1 2026 and expect it to be the first open-weight model to match closed frontier model performance on reasoning tasks."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "susan-li",
      "speaker_name": "Susan Li",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Revenue grew 19% to $51.8 billion. Operating income was $23.5 billion with a margin of 45.4%. Reality Labs revenue was $476 million, with operating loss of $4.4 billion, narrowing year-over-year. We are tracking full-year capex to land at approximately $65 billion. For Q4, we are guiding revenue of $54–58 billion."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Eric Sheridan at Goldman Sachs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-eric-sheridan",
      "speaker_name": "Eric Sheridan",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Susan, Reality Labs losses narrowing — is that a structural shift or a timing effect, and does Orion's consumer launch change the loss trajectory materially?"
    }
  ],
